In this proclamation issued by President Donald J. Trump on April 30, 2020, he declares May 2020 as Older Americans Month. The proclamation highlights the importance of older adults in society and acknowledges their contributions to the economy, defense of freedom, and shaping of the nation's character. The proclamation also recognizes the challenges faced by older Americans during the coronavirus pandemic and emphasizes the need to support and care for them during this time. President Trump mentions various actions his administration has taken to benefit older adults, such as lowering the cost of prescription drugs and improving access to medical care. He also emphasizes the vulnerability of older Americans to fraud and instructs the Department of Justice to prioritize protecting them from financial exploitation. The proclamation concludes by urging all Americans to honor and support older adults and reaffirming the country's commitment to them.